Five Maysville 5th and 6th grade teams competed in the Elementary School Quiz Bowl Competition in Cambridge on May 6th. The Sixth grade team, Crunchy Muffins, earned 1st place overall! Team members: Gaige Durant, Elijah Mayle, Shepp Cosgrave, and Owen Rusnak. Congratulations to all Quiz Bowlers!

Fifth grader, Auska Johnson was honored on Wednesday, May 8th, at Zane Trace Consortium for the Gifted's Annual Poetry Reading. Auska, pictured with ZTCG representative, Diane Schlegel, recited her poem, "A Soldier's Feelings", for the audience.

MHS Prom Information for Saturday, April 27:

Promenade - 5:00pm, Rear of the H.S. We are planning to have the promenade outside. Hopefully the weather cooperates. Please be prepared and bring an umbrella if needed. We will move the promenade to the M.S. gym only if the weather becomes severe.

The 21st Century Program presents:
THE GREAT HIGH SCHOOL WHODUNIT
An Audience-Participation Mystery by EILEEN MOUSHEY

Come join our Maysville Middle School cast for a night of murder mystery fun! The play will require the audience to complete tasks to earn clues to help solve the mystery of who killed Officer Randy Campbell and stole the Dudley Diamond.

When: Wednesday, March 27th. Doors open at 5:15pm, play begins at 6:00pm

Where: Maysville 6-12 Cafeteria

Admission: Admission will be by cash donation. All proceeds will go to Christ’s Table to help members within our community. Feel free to give as much or as little as you would like. Our performers decided to perform for you in order to help this local charity.

post_text: At PenOhio Regional, Marietta College: Maysville writers Jack Murphy, Kendra Roberts, and Sydni Wilson competed against teams from 5 other schools in writing narratives to 3 prompts. Maysville had the smallest team there, but took the top two JV prizes! Kendra Roberts won 1st Place, Jack Murphy won 2nd Place, and Sydni Wilson, in her first year of competing, made a strong showing with scores of a 1 and a 2 in the first two rounds of writing. Thanks to Shayna Moore, our van driver, and Sandra Rucker, board member, who chaperoned for us. It really is a great day to be a Panther!

STUDENT MAKE-UP DAYS
The use of calamity days has caused Maysville Local School District to make up 2 days. These days have been approved by the Board of Education. Students will attend school on May 29, 2019 and May 30, 2019. THE LAST DAY FOR STUDENTS IS MAY 30, 2019. Students will not be in school May 27-28 in celebration of Memorial Day.

Part of parents’ job is to protect their child(ren) from harm. Maysville Middle School wants to give you valuable information and parenting techniques to protect your child(ren) in this digital era. This will include information on the dangers and the consequences students may have when using social media, APPS, and online resources that leave a digital footprints. Deputy Saxton will be providing information along with a prosecutor from the Muskingum County… More

Dance: students can pay $3 to enter the dance that will be held during school hours. This is just a fun time for students, no need for students to bring extra clothes, come as you are! Students will be able to purchase $1 sundaes and water from student council during the dance!

Money is due in on Tuesday, December 18.

Pie in the face:
Students who brought in at least 15 canned goods for helping hands choose a staff member to pie in the face!!!

Winter Break Begins!!

post_text: Maysville Local School District is once again conducting the Maysville Helping Hands Program this year. Maysville students are encouraged to bring canned food items to school by December 7, to help families in our community this holiday season. Students can earn various prizes in each of the buildings. Maysville Elementary students can earn activity time and if the 3-5 grade students bring in 3000 cans, Mr. Winland’s head gets shaved! M.S. and H.S. Students can earn a pizza party or have an opportunity to throw a pie at a Principal while they are duct taped to a wall! Let’s join together and make this the best Maysville Helping Hands food drive to date!

post_text: Congratulations Rylee Butler! Maureen Montgomery from the Muskingum County Suicide Prevention Coalition presented Rylee with the Friends of Recovery Award sponsored by the Mental Health and Recovery Services Board.
